main event: The report describes a UFO sighting in Davenport, Iowa on March 6, 1968, where a ground observer saw a large, dark, elliptical object with a row of bright lights along the edge. The sighting was also tracked on radar for about 12 minutes.
interesting points: The object remained stationary for a short period, then began moving slowly away at an estimated speed of 75 mph.
As the object moved away, the radar blips became weaker and weaker until the object disappeared from the radarscope.
The report mentions that another case in Davenport, Iowa on March 3, 1963 involved a witness who observed and photographed a disc-shaped object near the Municipal Ball Park.
The report includes a handwritten letter from a witness describing a sighting of a large, oval-shaped, illuminated object that hovered silently for several minutes before ascending and disappearing.
The report contains a photographic data form with details about the camera, lens, film, and other settings used to photograph a UFO.
sighted object: a large, dark, elliptical object with a row of bright lights along the edge
photographs: yes, the report mentions photographs were taken in some cases, but the original negatives were not provided
